                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d308">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">752.00114/41: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mataro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-08-15T22:00:00+02:00"
                            >August 15, 1938—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 16—7:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1023. My 963, May 26, 3 p.m. The British Minister has informed me that the
                    negotiations for a mass exchange of prisoners have been concluded. The Spanish
                    plan transmitted with despatch No. 417 of June 4, has been modified and the
                    mediating commission will consist only of British members. It will be headed by
                    Sir Philip Chetwode and is expected to assemble within 10 days.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
